==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exculpation
<hw>Ex`cul*pa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>exculpatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of exculpating from alleged
fault or crime; that which exculpates; excuse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These robbers, however, were men who might have made out a strong
case in <qex>exculpation</qex> of themselves.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exculpatory</ent>⟦br⟧
